-- Jaeger CEO Earl Steps Down for Health Reasons, Times Reports
-- B y   G a v i n   F i n c h
-- 2012-03-17T10:25:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-17/jaeger-ceo-earl-steps-down-for-health-reasons-times-reports.html
Jaeger Group Ltd. Chief Executive
Officer Belinda Earl is stepping down for health reasons, the
Times of  London  reported, citing a company statement.  Carolyn Springett will replace Earl and also take charge of
the Aquascutum brand, the Times said. Jaeger is also cutting
about 20 jobs at its head office, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gavin Finch in London at 
 gfinch@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at 
 eevans3@bloomberg.net  